This paper focuses on privacy-preserving distributed machine learning algorithms, which involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), and distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy implications of their algorithm, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
